The highest priority comment is about regulation #2 and #4: The backend code must have a route for the root path '/' to serve the Dashboard page, and all frontend URLs must correspond exactly to backend routes.

Upon review, the backend code does define the '/' route with the function dashboard(), which renders 'dashboard.html'. The frontend buttons on the dashboard page use url_for('restaurants_page'), url_for('cart_page'), and url_for('active_orders_page'), which correspond to the backend routes '/restaurants', '/cart', and '/active_orders' respectively.

